        <h2>Common Issues with ITV Ice Makers</h2>
        <p>ITV ice makers require routine maintenance and timely repairs to function properly. Common issues include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice maker not producing ice</strong> – Often due to clogged water filters, faulty water inlet valves, or compressor failure.</li>
            <li><strong>Slow ice production</strong> – Caused by dirty condenser coils, low water pressure, or a malfunctioning thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Leaking water</strong> – Usually a result of a damaged pump, improper drainage, or broken water lines.</li>
            <li><strong>Irregular or misshapen ice cubes</strong> – Indicates issues with water flow, ice mold thermostat, or freezing cycles.</li>
            <li><strong>Unusual noises during operation</strong> – May point to worn-out fan motors, loose components, or failing bearings.</li>
        </ul>
        
